## 1 Kinetic Theory of Matter Quick recap from 'O' level Chemistry:

### Introduction

The Kinetic Theory of Matter describes the particles in solids, liquids and gases and the movement of these particles.

The bulk characteristics (i.e. physical properties) of matter can be explained by the **arrangement** and **movement** of the particles.

Many pure substances can exist in all of the three states of matter, depending on the conditions of the **temperature** and **pressure**.

